<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-06-11T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-06-11T17:00:00-05:00" n="183" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d183">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">883.05/162: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-06-11T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 11,
                                        1920—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>638. Your 887, June 3, 5 p.m., regarding judicial reforms in Egypt.</p>
                        <p>Department sees no objection at present to suggestion that negotiations
                            be conducted in London.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>